wtWebGraphAnalog57662ValuesTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662ValuesTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662ValuesTable.description: List of measurement values corresponding to the channel numbers.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662Values.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662Values
wtWebGraphAnalog57662Values.description: Measurement value of the sensor, ASCII. This value will be translated according to the ports settings for the read and write operations.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryValuesTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryValuesTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryValuesTable.description: List of binary measurement values corresponding to the channel numbers.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryValuesEntry.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryValuesEntry
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryValuesEntry.description: Binary measurement values of the sensors.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryValues.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryValues
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryValues.description: Binary measurement value of the sensor in 1/1000, signed number, 0x7FFFFFFF indicates an invalid value. This value will be translated according to the ports settings for the read and write operations.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlPassword.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlPassword
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlPassword.description: Entering this password opens a session which is ended by writing a 1 to wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlLogout. When read this variable provides a string of length zero.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlConfigMode.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlConfigMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlConfigMode.description: When the device is in SNMP configuration mode, the value 1 is returned, otherwise 0. If the read value is 0 even though the password was written, the device is already in config mode and the variables can only be read.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlLogout.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlLogout
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlLogout.description: If the device is in configuration mode and the session was opened by this SNMP Manager, writing a 1 to this variable will end the session and all parameters are stored. Writing a 2 discards all entries again. When read this variable provides the value 0.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlAdminPassw.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlAdminPassword
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlAdminPassw.description: This password protects access to the variables with administrator rights. It can only be changed by the administrator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlConfigPass.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlConfigPassword
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SessCntrlConfigPass.description: This password protects access to the variables with configurator rights. It can be changed by the administrator and by the configurator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public. When read this variable provides a null-pointer.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceName.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceName
wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceName.description: Name of the Webio, which is user definable.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceText.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceText
wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceText.description: Description of the Webio, which is user definable.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceLocation.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceLocation
wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceLocation.description: Description of the location of the Webio, which is user definable.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceContact.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceContact
wtWebGraphAnalog57662DeviceContact.description: Contact address of the system operator of the Webio, which is user definable.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662TzOffsetHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662TzOffsetHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57662TzOffsetHrs.description: Offset hours for the time zone (winter time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662TzOffsetMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662TzOffsetMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57662TzOffsetMin.description: Offset minutes for the time zone (winter time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662TzEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662TzEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662TzEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Timezone

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzOffsetHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzOffsetHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzOffsetHrs.description: Offset hours of the time zone (summer time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzOffsetMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzOffsetMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzOffsetMin.description: Offset minutes of the time zone (summer time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Summertime

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartMonth.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartMonth
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartMonth.description: Month in which the change is made from winter time to summer time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartMode.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartMode.description: Mode of the day of the week for which the change is made from winter time to summer time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartWday.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartWday
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartWday.description: Day of the week on which the change is made from winter time to summer time

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartHrs.description: Hour in which the time zone is changed from winter to summer time with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStartMin.description: Minute in which the time zone is changed from winter to summer time with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopMonth.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopMonth
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopMonth.description: Month in which the change is made from summer time to winter time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopMode.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopMode.description: Mode of the week day on which the change is made from summer time to winter time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopWday.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopWday
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopWday.description: Day of the week on which the change is made from summer time to winter time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopHrs.description: Hour at which the time zone is changed from summer to winter time with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57662StTzStopMin.description: Minute at which the time zone is changed from summer to winter time with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662TimeServer1.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662TimeServer1
wtWebGraphAnalog57662TimeServer1.description: IP address or name of the 1st time server in ASCII

wtWebGraphAnalog57662TimeServer2.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662TimeServer2
wtWebGraphAnalog57662TimeServer2.description: IP address or name of the 2nd time server in ASCII

wtWebGraphAnalog57662TsEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662TsEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662TsEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Time Server

wtWebGraphAnalog57662TsSyncTime.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662TsSyncTime
wtWebGraphAnalog57662TsSyncTime.description: Daily synchronisation time with the time server (hour: 0-23).

wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockHrs.description: Clock hours taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockMin.description: Clock minutes taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockDay.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockDay
wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockDay.description: Date: Day of the month, taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockMonth.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockMonth
wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockMonth.description: Date: Month, taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockYear.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockYear
wtWebGraphAnalog57662ClockYear.description: Date: Year, taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662DnsServer1.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662DnsServer1
wtWebGraphAnalog57662DnsServer1.description: IP address of the 1st DNS server in ASCII

wtWebGraphAnalog57662DnsServer2.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662DnsServer2
wtWebGraphAnalog57662DnsServer2.description: IP address of the 2nd DNS server in ASCII

wtWebGraphAnalog57662AddConfig.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662AddConfig
wtWebGraphAnalog57662AddConfig.description: Additional configuration (1=ON): Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1: DHCP disable Bit 0: BOOTP disable

wtWebGraphAnalog57662Startup.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662Startup
wtWebGraphAnalog57662Startup.description: Binary coded start page: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1: Index.htm Bit 2: Home.htm Bit 3: User.htm Only one page may be selected at a time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662GetHeaderEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662GetHeaderEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662GetHeaderEnable.description: If these bits are set, every answer of a short form GET question will be lead by the IP-address and name of the device and/or a HTTP header: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-6: unused Bit 1 : GET HTTP enable Bit 0 : GET Header enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57662HttpPort.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662HttpPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662HttpPort.description: Definition of the standard HTML port (Default: 80).

wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailReply.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailReply
wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailReply.description: Reply address for the mail server.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailServer.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailServer
wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailServer.description: Name or IP address of the mail server.

wtWebioAn1MailEnable.name: wtWebioAn1MailEnable
wtWebioAn1MailEnable.description: Set this bit to enable the sending of mails: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Mail enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailAuthentication.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailAuthentication
wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailAuthentication.description: Selection of the authentication modi: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : POP3 before SMTP Bit 1 : ESMTP, authentication Bit 0 : SMTP, no authentication

wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailAuthUser.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailAuthUser
wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailAuthUser.description: Name of the user to be authenticated.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailPop3Server.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailPop3Server
wtWebGraphAnalog57662MailPop3Server.description: Name or Ip-address of the POP3 Servers.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SystemTrapManagerIP.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SystemTrapManagerIP
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SystemTrapManagerIP.description: Name or IP address of the TCP server which accepts the system trap.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SystemTrapEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SystemTrapEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SystemTrapEnable.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SnmpEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SnmpEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SnmpEnable.description: Set bit 0 to enable SNMP. If disabled, the device did not respond to any SNMP requests. Bit 1 decided wether the community string of read operations is compared with the system password or not: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : SNMP enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57662UdpPort.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662UdpPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662UdpPort.description: Udp port to which the Udp queries ( short form GET requests) can be sent. This port number must be unique within the device.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662UdpEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662UdpEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662UdpEnable.description: Set this bit to enable UDP support: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : UDP enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogServerIP.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogServerIP
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the Syslog server, which accepts the Syslog messgaes.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogServerPort.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogServerPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogServerPort.description: Portnumber of the Syslog servers, default 514.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogSystemMessage.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogSystemMessagesEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogSystemMessage.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2: Diag Messages Bit 3-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SyslogEnable.description: Set bit 0to enable Syslog: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Syslog enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPServerIP.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPServerIP
wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the FTP server, which accepts the FTP messages.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPServerControlPor.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPServerControlPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPServerControlPor.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPOption.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPOption
wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPOption.description: Bit 0 switches the FTP Server in Passiv-Mode, the Client controls the data connection on its own: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : PASV enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662FTPEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable FTP: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : FTP enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57662LanguageSelect.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662LanguageSelect
wtWebGraphAnalog57662LanguageSelect.description: Language selection: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 2-7: unused Bit 1 : English Bit 0 : German

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTable.description: Table of properties of the binary mode.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryOperationMode.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryOperationMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryOperationMode.description: Selection of the operation mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : UDP Peer Bit 1 : TCP Client Bit 0 : TCP Server

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerLoca.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerLocalPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerLoca.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this server mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerInpu.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerInputTrigger
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerInpu.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input states. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Analog inputs 0-1

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerAppl.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerApplicationMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerAppl.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : OPC Device Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientLoca.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientLocalPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientLoca.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this client mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServ.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServerPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServ.description: Port number of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server port to zero.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServ.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServerIpAddr
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServ.description: Ip address of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServ.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServerPassword
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServ.description: Building a connection may be protected by the administrator password of the server. Enter the server password to establish the connection, if a server administrator password exists.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInac.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInactivity
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInac.description: Connection timeout in 100ms. If no data are exchanged within the specified time, the device closes the connection to the server. The value 0 deactivates the timer. Using the Box2Box mode this function is disabled.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInpu.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInputTrigger
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInpu.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input states. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Analog inputs 0-1

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInte.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInterval
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInte.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured application. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientAppl.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientApplicationMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientAppl.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerLocalP.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerLocalPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerLocalP.description: Local UDP port for data exchange in this peer to peer mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerRemote.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerRemotePort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerRemote.description: Port number of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote port to zero.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerRemote.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerRemoteIpAddr
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerRemote.description: Ip address of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote device IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerInputT.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerInputT.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input states. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Analog inputs 0-1

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerInterv.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerInterval
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerInterv.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured remote device. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerApplic.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerApplicationMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerApplic.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryConnectedPort.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryConnectedPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryConnectedPort.description: Port number of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations a zero will be read.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryConnectedIpAd.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryConnectedIpAddr
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryConnectedIpAd.description: IP address of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations 0.0.0.0 will be read.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerClie.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerClientHttpPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerClie.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Server Mode. If an mailfunction occurs status informations will be send to this port. Not used at mode Compatible 50xxx.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServ.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServerHttpPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientServ.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Client Mode. In the operating mode Box2Box connection status informations will be exchanged through this port.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerHyst.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerHysteresis1
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerHyst.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 1 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerHyst.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerHysteresis2
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerHyst.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 2 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpServerInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientHyst.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientHysteresis1
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientHyst.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 1 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientHyst.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientHysteresis2
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientHyst.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 2 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryTcpClientInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerHyster.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerHysteresis1
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerHyster.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 1 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerHyster.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerHysteresis2
wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerHyster.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 2 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57662BinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662LoggerTimebase.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662LoggerTimebase
wtWebGraphAnalog57662LoggerTimebase.description: Time base of the data logger

wtWebGraphAnalog57662LoggerSensorSel.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662LoggerSensorSel
wtWebGraphAnalog57662LoggerSensorSel.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Sensor 1 Bit 1: Sensor 2 Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57662DisplaySensorSel.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662DisplaySensorSel
wtWebGraphAnalog57662DisplaySensorSel.description: Binary coded sensor selection: only selected sensors will be shown in the graphical presentation: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Sensor 1 Bit 1: Sensor 2 Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SensorColorTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SensorColorTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SensorColorTable.description: List of sensor colors for the praphical presentation.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662SensorColor.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662SensorColor
wtWebGraphAnalog57662SensorColor.description: Color of the sensors at the praphical presention.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662AutoScaleEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662AutoScaleEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662AutoScaleEnable.description: If bit 0 is set, vertical auto scale is enabled: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Auto Scale enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57662VerticalUpperLimit.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662VerticalUpperLimit
wtWebGraphAnalog57662VerticalUpperLimit.description: This value defines the maximum temperature shown in the graphical presentation, if no auto scaling is selected. Temperature in degrees with maximum 2 decimal places.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662VerticalLowerLimit.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662VerticalLowerLimit
wtWebGraphAnalog57662VerticalLowerLimit.description: This value defines the minimum temperature shown in the graphical presentation, if no auto scaling is selected. Temperature in degrees with maximum 2 decimal places.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662HorizontalZoom.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662HorizontalZoom
wtWebGraphAnalog57662HorizontalZoom.description: Defines the default zoom stage, if no auto scaling is selected.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmTable.description: List of settings depending on the alarm number.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmEntry.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmEntry
wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmEntry.description: Alarm parameters of the individual alarms.

wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmTrigger.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmTrigger
wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmTrigger.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: Bit 0: Timer Bit 1: ColdStart Bit 2: WarmStart Octet 4: Bit 0: Sensor 1 Bit 1: Sensor 2 Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmMin1.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmMin1

wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmTimerCron.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmTimerCron
wtWebGraphAnalog57662AlarmTimerCron.description: This entry defines a time window for alarm 1-8 and a activation time for the report. A time window is definied by start and stop time stamp, seperated by a space or tab. The activation time of the report is defined by a single start time stamp. Each time stamp contains 5 space or tab seperated text fields for time trigger definition. Each field must match with the actual time to trigger an action, weekday and day of month are interpreted separatley. 1: Minutes Range 0-59 2. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 3: Day of month Range 1-31 4: Month Range 1-12 5: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas (i.e.: 2,14,22) - a partition within the allowed range (i.e.: 1-5) - step size within a partition of the allowed range (i.e.: 0-59/2 every second minute).

If Auto adaptive is selected, the optimal value of wtWebGraphAnalog57662PortCompensationValue will be determinate continuously. Set Bit 1 to start with the last saved value of wtWebGraphAnalog57662PortCompensationValue in this Mode. If Bit 0 is cleared and Auto Mode is off wtWebGraphAnalog57662PortCompensationValue will allways be used, regardless of the state of Bit 1. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit,Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB.
